{
  "texts": [
    "Here are some common specific traffic scene datasets and brief introductions to them.",
    "Traffic Sign and Traffic Light DatasetsWidely used traffic sign detection datasets at this stage include the German Traffic Sign Benchmark (GTSB) [77] (consisting of the German Traffic Sign Recognition Benchmark (GTSRB) [78]and the German Traffic Sign Detection Benchmark (GTSDB) [79].GTSRB contains a single traffic sign in each image and is therefore suitable for solving object classification problems.",
    "The dataset contains 43 types of traffic signs, with 39,209 training images and 12,630 test images.",
    "These images have different lighting conditions and complex backgrounds.GTSDB contains 900 images, of which 600 are used for training and the remaining 300 for validation.The TT100K dataset [80] was compiled and released by the joint laboratory of Tsinghua University and Tencent.",
    "It provides 100,000 images containing 30,000 traffic signs."
  ]
}